1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,400
Ever wonder why things fall apart?

2
00:00:02,400 --> 00:00:03,600
It’s called entropy.

3
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:05,600
In physics, entropy measures disorder.

4
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:08,400
The universe naturally favors chaos over neatness.

5
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:10,000
Imagine a tidy room.

6
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,800
Over time, it becomes a chaotic mess.

7
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:14,400
That’s entropy in action.

8
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:19,200
The second law of thermodynamics states that total entropy can never decrease.

9
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:20,800
It’s a one-way street.

10
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:22,800
This principle isn’t just theory.

11
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:27,600
It drives engines, powers reactions, and defines the flow of time itself.

12
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:30,800
Want to dive deeper into the universe’s secrets?

13
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:33,200
Hit subscribe and explore with me.
